<h1>Food Transparency UK</h1>

<p class="lede">{{ site.tagline }}</p>

<p>Food Transparency UK is an evidence-based archive of packaged foods sold in the United Kingdom. It explains what these foods contain, how their recipes have changed over time, and why those changes happened. The aim is to make the gap between what a food used to be and what it is now visible and traceable.</p>

<p>It is written first for the ordinary shopper, in plain English, with jargon defined where it appears. Journalists, researchers, teachers and policymakers are served by the same records.</p>

<p>Every published fact shows its source, its date, and two grades: how confident the curator is in the record, and how strong the evidence behind it is. Nothing is asserted without provenance, and gaps are shown honestly rather than hidden.</p>

<p><a href="{{ '/methodology/' | url }}">Read the methodology</a> to see how sources, confidence and evidence are recorded.</p>
